Humming Eagle,<br><br>
?????????????<br><br>
&quot;I am like &quot;Makamnaya,&quot; those who go smelling like a skunk.&quot;<br><br>
A man who smells like a skunk is also one who has crossed the skunk's path by accident. That is different than being the skunk. When many men cross the skunks path, they do not judge each other with the smell they all carry. There are enough skunks in the world without making more of them. It is better to wash and laugh, and let the skunk go on its way, than all share in its skin.<br><br>
&quot;I have scorned a fellow warrior, Kola Icamani, a quiet brother who walked alongside of me.&quot;<br><br>
Each warrior has two ways. The way of his people and the way of himself. Sometimes, the way of himself may seem to contradict the way of his people. It is only in battle with fellow warriors that he displays this seeming contradiction. Among fellow warriors this is understood and accepted. They are all human, after all. I went out this morning and watched the birds awaken. They began the hunt. I saw that they all flew a little differently, but they still all flew and flew together. I have yet to see a skunk fly. Have you?<br><br>
&quot;I will understand why others look away from me.&quot;<br><br>
I am looking right at you. Others are looking right at you. Only when the warrior harms his people will we then look away. If a warrior says &quot;This is how I feel, and I command recognition.&quot;, he is also looking at himself. There is honor in that, and that honor is respected, not shamed. Sometimes, it makes other warriors look at themselves, too. If everyone is in sad shape, it is time for the Ceremony of the Sweat Lodge. In that way, all are reborn to begin again. The four endurances bring all warriors back to the common ground.<br><br>
We need a &quot;cyber&quot; sweat lodge, and it is right here!<br><br>
As you can see, I have done some reading.<br><br>
Hecito Yelo, my Brother of Choice.  <br><br>
  <br><br>

